  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "LLMs are relatively new in the AI landscape, at least if we focus on transformer-based architectures (Vaswani et al., 2017).",
    "Among other things, these systems, trained on huge datasets, can produce impressively convincing texts on the basis of prompts given by the users.",
    "While transformer-based LLMs have been available for some years now, they have become extremely popular among the general public after OpenAI's launch of ChatGPT in November 2022.",
    "From a technical point of view, ChatGPT was not dramatically revolutionary: it was based on a pre-existing model that was fine-tuned to make it suitable for conversation.",
    "From a more societal perspective, however, it was groundbreaking: since November 2022, everyone has the possibility to interact free of charge and through a user-friendly interface with a state-of-the-art language model that impressively performs in a number of tasks, generating textual outputs that are often hardly distinguishable from human-produced ones."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "LLMs are relatively new in the AI landscape, at least if we focus on transformer-based architectures (Vaswani et al., 2017)."
  ]
